shared_text:
Estelle Kampmeyer Elementary PTO O'Fallon IL
August 27 at 8:16 PM ·

Celebration of Asher Elijah Austin

Hello, We really appreciate your love and support during this time.
Visitation will be from 2:00-3:00pm on Sunday, August 30th at First Baptist Church OFallon (limited capacity) if you would like to stop by. Due to capacity limits, we hope you will join us via live stream for Asher's Celebration of Life. It will begin at 3:00pm.
www.fbcofallon.org/asher

EK students, staff, and friends are encouraged to join us at OFallon Community Park between 4:00-8:00pm to paint rocks in Asher's memory. A balloon release will take place at 5:30pm. Social distancing and masks please.

Also, please take a few minutes to post a memory and/or photo on Kudoboard. https://www.kudoboard.com/boards/01wrXvgw

Good morning, D90,
We know you still have many questions and we want to answer as many as we can for you. We also respect that you would like questions answered as soon as possible. We are compiling an FAQ document so that there is one central location for the answers to your questions. This will help families all have access to the same information in one location rather than trying to locate it in various posts or comments.
Questions can be sent to chruby@of90.net. We will share as many answers as we can via the FAQ and will continuously update it.
Thank you!

They have cool gear and proceeds are used to purchase gift cards from local businesses that are given to healthcare providers and first responders!

Moye second graders learned about fractions last week. Students asked their family members what pizza toppings they would like on their pizza, recorded their answers, drew equal parts on their pizzas, and illustrated and wrote fractions to depict their findings.
Second grader, Kierstin (Mrs. Vahle's class), decided to MAKE her family her fraction pizza for dinner. Great job, Kierstin!

District 90's in-person registration process that was scheduled for May 6th at your child's home school has been cancelled.
District 90 will reopen the online registration process for returning families during the week of May 4th - 8th. Once this window closes, the next scheduled registration date will be July 23rd from 3 pm to 6:30 pm at your child's home school. The July registration will be open to returning and new families to District 90.

Please email your child's office staff if you need assistance with the online registration process.

Schaefer Kindergarten teacher Mrs. Holley put a positive twist on this tough pandemic situation. Each year her students spend the last 26 days celebrating letters and learning. While she was heartbroken that they can't do all the activities they usually do (like a trip to the zoo for letter Z), she adjusted and planned some fun remote lessons. Today her students invited Principal Duggins to celebrate letter Y with yoga. Assistant Principal Ganey will join them on Wednesday for story time.
Keep up the great work, D90!

April is the Month of the Military Child. A military child is a child whose parent or parents are serving in the military.

Did you know that approximately 2 million military children have experienced a parental deployment since 2001? To the military kids that had a parent that currently is or has been deployed, thank you for your service!

Did you know military families relocate 10 times more often than civilian families, on average, every 2-3 years? That is a lot of moving and changing schools. We are glad to have you at O'Fallon District 90!

Effective immediately the City of O'Fallon has now closed:
All Playground Equipment,
All Pavilions,
All Basketball courts,
Batting Cages by Diamond #1,
Diamond #1,
Skate Park.

These changes have been made after observation of large groups and gatherings and/or lack of attention to distancing requirements.The City would like to keep property open for families and individuals to get out and walk, run and exercise, but will continue to monitor for compliance.

In line with the above, groups are also prohibited from using school grounds. Individuals may walk/run/exercise on district property, but large groups are not allowed to congregate or gather.

Please ensure social distancing practices for your own safety and the safety of our community! Thank you

post_text:
O'Fallon Mayor Herb Roach asks the schools to remind our followers of the IMPORTANCE of social distancing.
Please, please, do NOT go to the parks to play basketball with a group of friends. Do not gather in parks or other areas.

The City hopes to be able to keep parks open for walkers/joggers who socially distance--BUT gatherings of people and kids who are playing basketball, soccer, baseball or using pavilions can further the spread and increase closures.

We all need to do our part to get beyond this as soon as possible, and to not overwhelm our hospitals. The peaks are expected to come sometime between April 9 and 18, and more social gatherings will prolong or intensify this.

post_text:
Parents/Guardians--
As you know the window for D90 online registration for 2020-2021 is now open. You may log in to your Skyward Family Access to register.

Regarding fee payments--You may now pay online, but if you prefer to pay via check, please do so by mail to your school between May 4- May 15. This will allow our secretaries a window in which to receive the mail and make the deposits safely. Please be sure to make note that the payment is for 2020-2021 registration and include your child's name.
Once your payment is received and all documents are uploaded/completed, the registration process is complete. Each school will issue receipts for your records.

* If you have students in different buildings, please mail the check to one school and include all of the students' names/schools on a note enclosed in the envelope.

Thank you!

post_text:
Updated at 1:14 pm--The ClassLink issue appears to have been resolved. Thank you for your patience.

We're receiving reports of apps not appearing correctly on both teacher and student ClassLink dashboards this morning.

ClassLink sent out emails about a service disruption with their Roster Server, which we utilize for IXL, Discovery Education, BrainPop and a few other apps. These appear to be the apps that are affected at this time.

Initially, the service issue only affected access to the Roster Server management page, but it appears it is also affecting the apps tied to that service.

The good news is ClassLink is aware of the issue and is actively working on resolving it. The District will continue to monitor the status of the resolution and provide an update when able.

Dear D90 Parents/Guardians—As planned, the D90 online registration window opens today. When you are ready please begin the process by completing the steps in Skyward Family Access but delay fee payments until at least Wednesday. We are exploring options that may be more convenient and will have more information about where to send checks or how to complete that step online.

Here are the steps to complete registration but hold on fees for now:

We strongly encourage everyone to be very cautious when listening to or spreading rumors. A good rule of thumb for everyone right now is--If you didn't hear something from the CDC, IDPH, ISBE, Govt Officials, or the District, please do not trust it or spread it. Rather, ask questions about the validity and research it further. There are many rumors being circulated and causing additional anxiety in an already stressful time. We are relying on the above for information and ask all of our families to do the same.

One way to avoid rumors is to go straight to the source. Below is the link to Governor Pritzker's press conferences: https://www2.illinois.gov/cms/agency/media/radio/pages/default.aspx

On Tuesday and Wednesday, O'Fallon-Shiloh schools relied on the organization of volunteers (Cornerstone Church, Feed My Lambs, the YMCA and First Methodist Church) and local businesses (see below) for free meals to be delivered to students.
Please help us thank them all for their donations to student lunches:
Jersey Mikes donated 100 bags of chips and 4 dozen cookies.
Crazy Bowls and Wraps donated 400 bags of chips and 400 mini krispie bites.
Honey Baked Ham donated 50 lunches.
Chickfila donated 450 nugget/chicken sandwiches.
Sweet Katie Bee's donated 50 lunches.
Feed My Lambs, Cornerstone Church, the Y and First Methodist Church supplemented the donations and organized the deliveries.

Free meals to students-in-need now continue via our food service vendor, Sodexo and the other districts' food vendors, Aramark and Belleville 118.

We are overwhelmed by the generosity of O'Fallon-Shiloh!
We can do this!

post_text:
There is a great deal of information online regarding COVID-19. The healthcare professionals remind us that the "go to" place for information is the CDC whose resources are constantly being updated. Be sure to check the dates of any information you receive, as information is changing.

In addition to washing your hands, please also strengthen your immune system.
--Get enough sleep, proper nutrition, exercise.
--Disinfect commonly touched places and items (including cell phones and door knobs).
--Practice social distancing and stay at home if you’re feeling ill.
--Reduce stress as much as possible. This is important for our children! We know that children absorb the emotions and stress of the adults in their lives and this can create trauma because they feel out of control. Help your children feel your calm approach to prevention.

The City of O’Fallon hosted a meeting for local leaders from our schools, churches, hospitals, daycares, assisted living facilities and neighboring communities about COVID-19. We covered the facts about this virus and discussed what we can do to help combat the spread of COVID-19. O’Fallon is united and working together to keep this community safe and healthy.

At this time, there are no confirmed cases of COVID-19 in O’Fallon or St. Clair County.

We will continue to provide updates that we receive about COVID-19.

post_text:
Schools remain in session, but we must also consider attendance at large events. The CDC recommends practicing social distancing as one of several preventative measures. Due to the fact that the Annual Fine Arts Festival draws very large, standing room-only crowds, social distancing is very difficult at this event, and crowds may come from outside of our region. Therefore the Fine Arts Festival that was scheduled for tonight at Fulton is being cancelled.

There are many factors to consider when making decisions about cancellations of events. Notification of any additional cancellations will be shared as needed. We appreciate your understanding.

We are very proud to let you know that our D90 Fine Arts Faculty plan to record some student performances and share them online soon. We applaud them for thinking outside the box and being flexible while precautions are implemented. Bravo to them for that idea!

post_text:
We all play a role in reducing the likelihood of a coronavirus outbreak in our school district community. We encourage everyone to practice good habits, including:
--Wash your hands regularly, especially after using the restroom and before preparing or consuming food. Using soap and hot water, wash for about 20 seconds. Be sure to also wash your fingertips.
--Avoid coughing or sneezing into your hands or in the air.
--Always try to cough or sneeze into a tissue, and then throw the tissue away. If you don’t have a tissue, cough/sneeze into your arm.
--As much as you can, avoid touching your eyes, mouth and nose.
--If children are feeling sick, please keep them home from school. Allow them some time to feel better so that they do not risk infecting others.

Mrs. Ashley Frey was then recognized for her heartfelt support to students, as evidenced by the impact she made on Fulton graduate and OTHS student, Donnie Simpson.

We thank Judge Grandy and Catina Simpson for recognizing them as examples of the excellent educators in District 90.

D90 has used 4 snow days/weather cancellation days thus far this school year.

At their meeting last night, the Board of Education approved an amendment to the 2019-20 calendar (current school year) to make up the snow/weather cancellation days we have used so far.
November 12, 2019 cancellation will be made up on May 21, 2020.
December 16, 2019 cancellation will be made up on May 22, 2020.
December 17, 2019 cancellation will be made up on May 26, 2020.
January 17, 2020 cancellation will be made up on May 27, 2020.

Should another cancellation be necessary, the last day of school will move to May 28, 2020.

Good morning,
Although it is not typical that we would send a message when school is IN session, district officials want to confirm that D90 plans to have school and to run at the regular times. Parking lots and sidewalks are being treated for extra precaution. Please use extra caution on sidewalks and parking lots in case any slush or slick spots remain.

As part of a recent grant, O’Fallon Rotary Club Rotarians volunteer their time to read to D90 students. The Club also donated $2,700 to be used for high quality reading materials and scholarships via the O’Fallon Early Childhood Development Foundation.

We thank the Rotary Club of O’Fallon for their generous gifts of time and financial support! Our students LOVE having the special visitors read to them!

https://www.earlychildhoodofallon.org/

Celebrating the holiday season with D90 at the O’Fallon Illuminated Parade!
Thanks to our awesome float team, the Seipp family, and our generous and supportive sponsor, Warma Witter Kreisler Insurance! Our float wouldn’t have been possible without you!
We also thank the many parade organizers who brought this wonderful tradition to our town, and saved Christmas!
